headline: 1 Healthcare Stock to Own for Decades and 2 That Underwhelm
summary: Personal health and wellness is one of the many secular tailwinds for healthcare companies. But speed bumps such as inventory destockings have persisted in the wake of COVID-19, and over the past six months, the industry has pulled back by 9.3%. This drop is a stark contrast from the S&P 500’s 5.4% gain.

headline: UNH Q2 Deep Dive: Margin Compression Spurs Broad Management Overhaul and Strategy Reset
summary: Health insurance company UnitedHealth (NYSE:UNH) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 12.9% year on year to $111.6 billion. On the other hand, the company’s full-year revenue guidance of $446.8 billion at the midpoint came in 0.5% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $4.08 per share was 8.3% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
